Three fixes needed:

1. **CRITICAL — Add EventBus to RaidReviewService**: The service currently does not emit any events after approve/reject/retry. This blocks NIU-240 (Notifications) from knowing when reviews happen. Add EventBus as a constructor parameter to RaidReviewService. After each state transition (approve -> MERGED, reject -> FAILED, retry -> PENDING), emit a raid.state_changed event via the EventBus with raid_id, new status, and any relevant data (pr_url, confidence score). Update all callers (raids.py REST endpoints and telegram webhook) to pass the EventBus when constructing the service.

2. **find_raid_by_tracker_id should be abstract on the port**: Currently it has a default return None implementation. Make it @abstractmethod on RaidRepository and implement it in PostgresRaidRepository with a proper SQL query: SELECT * FROM raids WHERE tracker_id = $1. This ensures tracker-ID lookups actually work in production. Update any other adapters/stubs that implement RaidRepository to add the method.

3. **Fix the else: block in webhook secret validation**: Per project code style rules, no single-line else. Restructure to use early return:
   if not telegram_cfg.webhook_secret:
       logger.warning(...)
   elif token != telegram_cfg.webhook_secret:
       return Response(status_code=403)

Fix all three, run tests, commit, push.
